Even copyleft licenses like the GPLv3 or Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike (CC BY-SA) still use the term "copyright" in the legal text because:

Copyright is the legal framework that makes copyleft possible.

Copyleft is not the absence of copyright, itâ€™s a strategy that uses copyright law to enforce openness and freedom.